-- Standard Chartered Appoints New Global Head of Structured Equity
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   G a r v e y
-- 2012-03-20T03:13:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/standard-chartered-appoints-new-global-head-of-structured-equity.html
Standard Chartered Plc said it
hired Steven Phan as a managing director and Hong Kong-based
 global head  of structured equity.  Phan reports to Ed Steel, global head of equity derivatives
trading, and Raghavan Rajagopalan, global co-head of structuring
for financial markets, the London-based bank said in an e-mailed
statement yesterday.  Phan worked in London for HSBC Holdings Plc from 2005 to
2011, most recently as global head of investments, access and
structured solutions, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Garvey in  Hong Kong  at 
